@sadrasabouri 
I updated `Doucment.ipynb` and `README.md`.
Please take a look at my comments 💯

IMO, I confess that I don't really understand the motivation for gloming this functionality on to the existing classifier test when this is really an entirely separate, independent check. Conflated them, as well as implementing rather complex handling of various interactions between them, just complicates the logic and implementation of the existing check and furthermore makes what is already the longest and most complicated check even longer and more complicated. This adds technical risk to this PR, making reviewing and testing it more difficult and increases future maintenance burden, for little clear gain.

Instead of doing all this, I would instead advise just making it a separate check, and simply tweaking the message of the existing check to be specific to the version classifiers. I.e., as I suggested on the issue, just

```python
class PythonVersionRequires(BaseTest):
    weight = 100

    def test(self, data):
        requires_python = data.get("requires_python")
        if not requires_python:
            return False
        try:
            packaging.specifiers.SpecifierSet(requires_python)
        except packaging.specifiers.InvalidSpecifier:
            return False
        return True

    def message(self):
        return (
            "You should specify what Python versions you support "
            "with a valid version specifier in the "
            "requires-python/python_requires metadata key"
        )
```
